21/02/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Bosnian director Jasmila Zbanic, whose film "Grbavica" won the prestigious Golden Bear award at the weekend's 56th Berlin Film Festival, got a warm homecoming Monday (20 February). Dozens of people -- actors, directors, journalists, representatives of the Sarajevo Film Festival and others -- applauded Zbanic at the Sarajevo Airport. The Bosnian premiere of "Grbavica", which examines the aftermath of mass rape during the siege of Sarajevo, is planned for 1 March. (Dnevni avaz - 21/02/06; pincom.info, Fena - 20/02/06)
